"title": "5583: tools",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5583: tools",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Implements used for agricultural or mechanical purposes. Early tools were of wood, flint or stone. The development of ironworking brought iron-bladed tools and farm implements into common use. Axes were used to fell trees; hammers, chisels and saws were used by both carpenters and masons. Assyria and Babylon are depicted as tools in God's hand.</p>\n<h2>Tools made from iron and bronze</h2>\n<h3>General references</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:22\">GEN 4:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:31\">2SA 12:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr20:3\">1CH 20:3</a> <em>saws, iron picks and axes</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:7\">2SA 23:7</a> <em>iron tools</em></p>\n<h3>Iron axe-heads</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:4-2Kgs6:5\">2KI 6:4–6:5</a></strong> <em>Axes comprised an iron head fitted to a wooden shaft.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:5\">DEU 19:5</a></p>\n<h3>Sharpening iron tools</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:19-1Sam13:21\">1SA 13:19–13:21</a></strong> <em>A ploughshare is the cutting blade of a plough. A mattock is a large pick with a flat edge used for loosening soil and cutting.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:10\">ECC 10:10</a></p>\n<h2>Tools used in specific tasks</h2>\n<h3>Axes used for felling trees</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:48\">JDG 9:48</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:19-Deut20:20\">DEU 20:19–20:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:5-Ps74:6\">PSA 74:5–74:6</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:10\">MAT 3:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:9\">LUK 3:9</a> <em>Felling trees with an axe as a symbol of judgment.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:22-Jer46:23\">JER 46:22–46:23</a></p>\n<h3>Woodworking tools</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:13\">ISA 44:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:6\">EXO 21:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:17\">DEU 15:17</a> <em>awl</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:3-Jer10:4\">JER 10:3–10:4</a> <em>chisel, hammer and nails</em></p>\n<h3>Metalworking tools</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:24\">JOB 19:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:36\">EXO 28:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:30\">EXO 39:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:1\">JER 17:1</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:7\">ISA 41:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:4\">EXO 32:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:12\">ISA 44:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:9\">JER 10:9</a></p>\n<h3>Stoneworking tools</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:7\">1KI 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:9\">1KI 7:9</a></strong> <em>Saws were used in both carpentry and stonemasonry.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:1\">EXO 34:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:3\">DEU 10:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:16\">ISA 22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:29\">JER 23:29</a>EXO <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:25\">20:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:5\">DEU 27:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:31\">JOS 8:31</a></p>\n<h3>Agricultural tools</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:4\">ISA 2:4</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:3\">MIC 4:3</a> <em>A pruning hook is a curved blade used in pruning.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:10\">JOL 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa18:5\">ISA 18:5</a> <em>pruning knives</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:24\">ISA 30:24</a> <em>fork and shovel</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:7\">JER 15:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:12\">MAT 3:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:17\">LUK 3:17</a></p>\n<h2>The nations as tools in God's hand</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:15\">ISA 10:15</a></strong> <em>Assyria is used by God to punish his people.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa10:5\">ISA 10:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:23\">JER 50:23</a> <em>Babylon is a hammer in God's hand.</em></p>",
